#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:732
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting and stopping Apache"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:734
#, no-c-format
msgid "If configured with &yast; as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-configuration-yast\"/> , Apache is started at boot time in the <systemitem>multi-user.target</systemitem> and <systemitem>graphical.target</systemitem> . You can change this behavior using &yast;'s <guimenu>&ycc_runlevel;</guimenu> or with the <command>systemctl</command> command line tool ( <command>systemctl enable</command> or <command>systemctl disable</command> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:744
#, no-c-format
msgid "To start, stop or manipulate Apache on a running system, use either the <command>systemctl</command> or the <command>apachectl</command> commands as described below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:750
#, no-c-format
msgid "For general information about <command>systemctl</command> commands, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-boot-systemd-basics-services\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:757
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>systemctl status apache2.service</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:759
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checks if Apache is started."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:765
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>systemctl start apache2.service</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:767
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starts Apache if it is not already running."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:775
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stops Apache by terminating the parent process."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:781
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>systemctl restart apache2.service</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:783
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stops and then restarts Apache. Starts the Web server if it was not running before."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:790
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>systemctl try-restart apache2.service</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:792
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stops then restarts Apache only if it is already running."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:798
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>systemctl reload apache2.service</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:800
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stops the Web server by advising all forked Apache processes to first finish their requests before shutting down. As each process dies, it is replaced by a newly started one, resulting in a complete <quote>restart</quote> of Apache."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:807
#, no-c-format
msgid "Restarting Apache in production environments"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:808
#, no-c-format
msgid "This command allows activating changes in the Apache configuration without causing connection break-offs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:842
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>systemctl stop apache2.service</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:844
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stops the Web server after a defined period of time configured with <systemitem>GracefulShutdownTimeout</systemitem> to ensure that existing requests can be finished."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:852
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>apachectl configtest</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:854
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checks the syntax of the configuration files without affecting a running Web server. Because this check is forced every time the server is started, reloaded or restarted, it is usually not necessary to run the test explicitly (if a configuration error is found, the Web server is not started, reloaded or restarted)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:864
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>apachectl status</command> and <command>apachectl fullstatus</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:866
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dumps a short or full status screen, respectively. Requires the module <systemitem>mod_status</systemitem> to be enabled and a text-based browser (such as <command>links</command> or <command>w3m</command> ) to be installed. Besides that, <literal>STATUS</literal> must be added to <systemitem>APACHE_SERVER_FLAGS</systemitem> in the file <filename>/etc/sysconfig/apache2</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:916
#, no-c-format
msgid "Additional flags"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:917
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you specify additional flags to the commands, these are passed through to the Web server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:924
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing, activating and configuring modules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:926
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Apache software is built in a modular fashion: all functionality except certain core tasks are handled by modules. This has progressed so far that even HTTP is processed by a module ( <systemitem>http_core</systemitem> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:932
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apache modules can be compiled into the Apache binary at build time or be dynamically loaded at runtime. Refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-modules-activating\"/> for details of how to load modules dynamically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:939
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apache modules are organized into the following categories:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:945
#, no-c-format
msgid "Base modules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:947
#, no-c-format
msgid "Base modules are compiled into Apache by default. Apache in &productname; has only <systemitem>mod_so</systemitem> (needed to load other modules) and <systemitem>http_core</systemitem> compiled in. All others are available as shared objects: rather than being included in the server binary itself, they can be included at runtime."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:957
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extension modules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:959
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modules labeled as extensions are included in the Apache software package, but are usually not compiled into the server statically. In &productname;, they are available as shared objects that can be loaded into Apache at runtime."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:970
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modules labeled external are not included in the official Apache distribution. However, &productname; provides several of them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:977
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multiprocessing modules (MPMs)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:979
#, no-c-format
msgid "MPMs are responsible for accepting and handling requests to the Web server, representing the core of the Web server software."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:988
#, no-c-format
msgid "Module installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:989
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you have done a default installation as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-quickstart-installation\"/> , the following modules are already installed: all base and extension modules, the multiprocessing module Prefork MPM, and the external module <systemitem>mod_python</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:996
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can install additional external modules by starting &yast; and choosing <menuchoice><guimenu>Software</guimenu> <guimenu>Software Management</guimenu></menuchoice> . Now choose <menuchoice><guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenu>Search</guimenu></menuchoice> and search for <literal>apache</literal> . Among other packages, the results list contains all available external Apache modules."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1007
#, no-c-format
msgid "Activation and deactivation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1008
#, no-c-format
msgid "Activate or deactivate particular modules either manually or with &yast;. In &yast;, script language modules (PHP &php-version; and Python) need to be enabled or disabled with the module configuration described in <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-configuration-yast-wizard\"/> . All other modules can be enabled or disabled as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-configuration-yast-server-configuration-modules\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1016
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you prefer to activate or deactivate the modules manually, use the commands <command>a2enmod</command> <replaceable>MODULE</replaceable> or <command>a2dismod</command> <replaceable>MODULE</replaceable> , respectively. <command>a2enmod -l</command> outputs a list of all currently active modules."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1024
#, no-c-format
msgid "Including configuration files for external modules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1025
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you have activated external modules manually, make sure to load their configuration files in all virtual host configurations. Configuration files for external modules are located under <filename>/etc/apache2/conf.d/</filename> and are loaded in <filename>/etc/apache2/default-server.conf</filename> by default. For more fine-grained control you can comment out the inclusion in <filename>/etc/apache2/default-server.conf</filename> and add it to specific virtual hosts only. See <filename>/etc/apache2/vhosts.d/vhost.template</filename> for examples."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1040
#, no-c-format
msgid "Base and extension modules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1041
#, no-c-format
msgid "All base and extension modules are described in detail in the Apache documentation. Only a brief description of the most important modules is available here. Refer to <link xlink:href=\"https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/\">http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/</link> to learn details about each module."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1050
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_actions</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1052
#, no-c-format
msgid "Provides methods to execute a script whenever a certain MIME type (such as <systemitem>application/pdf</systemitem> ), a file with a specific extension (like <filename>.rpm</filename> ), or a certain request method (such as <systemitem>GET</systemitem> ) is requested. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1062
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_alias</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1064
#, no-c-format
msgid "Provides <systemitem>Alias</systemitem> and <systemitem>Redirect</systemitem> directives with which you can map a URL to a specific directory ( <systemitem>Alias</systemitem> ) or redirect a requested URL to another location. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1073
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_auth*</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1075
#, no-c-format
msgid "The authentication modules provide different authentication methods: basic authentication with <systemitem>mod_auth_basic</systemitem> or digest authentication with <systemitem>mod_auth_digest</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1080
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_auth_basic</systemitem> and <systemitem>mod_auth_digest</systemitem> must be combined with an authentication provider module, <systemitem>mod_authn_*</systemitem> (for example, <systemitem>mod_authn_file</systemitem> for text file&ndash;based authentication) and with an authorization module <systemitem>mod_authz_*</systemitem> (for example, <systemitem>mod_authz_user</systemitem> for user authorization)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1089
#, no-c-format
msgid "More information about this topic is available in the <citetitle>Authentication HOWTO</citetitle> at <link xlink:href=\"https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/howto/auth.html\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1097
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_auth_openidc</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1099
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_auth_openidc</systemitem> the only certified way to use OpenID Connect with the Apache HTTP server. (See <link xlink:href=\"https://openid.net/developers/certified-openid-connect-implementations/\"/> .)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1107
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_autoindex</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Autoindex generates directory listings when no index file (for example, <filename>index.html</filename> ) is present. The look and feel of these indexes is configurable. This module is enabled by default. However, directory listings are disabled by default via the <systemitem>Options</systemitem> directive&mdash;overwrite this setting in your virtual host configuration. The default configuration file for this module is located at <filename>/etc/apache2/mod_autoindex-defaults.conf</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1122
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_cgi</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1124
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_cgi</systemitem> is needed to execute CGI scripts. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1131
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_deflate</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1133
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using this module, Apache can be configured to compress given file types on the fly before delivering them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1140
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_dir</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1142
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_dir</systemitem> provides the <systemitem>DirectoryIndex</systemitem> directive with which you can configure which files are automatically delivered when a directory is requested ( <filename>index.html</filename> by default). It also provides an automatic redirect to the correct URL when a directory request does not contain a trailing slash. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1153
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_env</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Controls the environment that is passed to CGI scripts or SSI pages. Environment variables can be set or unset or passed from the shell that invoked the <systemitem class=\"daemon\">httpd</systemitem> process. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1164
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_expires</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1166
#, no-c-format
msgid "With <systemitem>mod_expires</systemitem> , you can control how often proxy and browser caches refresh your documents by sending an <systemitem>Expires</systemitem> header. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1175
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_http2</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1177
#, no-c-format
msgid "With <systemitem>mod_http2</systemitem> , Apache gains support for the HTTP/2 protocol. It can be enabled by specifying <literal>Protocols h2 http/1.1</literal> in a <systemitem>VirtualHost</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1185
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_include</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1187
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_include</systemitem> lets you use Server Side Includes (SSI), which provide a basic functionality to generate HTML pages dynamically. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1195
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_info</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1197
#, no-c-format
msgid "Provides a comprehensive overview of the server configuration under http://localhost/server-info/. For security reasons, you should always limit access to this URL. By default only <systemitem class=\"domainname\">localhost</systemitem> is allowed to access this URL. <systemitem>mod_info</systemitem> is configured at <filename>/etc/apache2/mod_info.conf</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1208
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_log_config</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1210
#, no-c-format
msgid "With this module, you can configure the look of the Apache log files. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1217
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_mime</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1219
#, no-c-format
msgid "The mime module ensures that a file is delivered with the correct MIME header based on the file name's extension (for example <systemitem>text/html</systemitem> for HTML documents). This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_negotiation</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1230
#, no-c-format
msgid "Necessary for content negotiation. See <link xlink:href=\"https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/content-negotiation.html\">http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/content-negotiation.html</link> for more information. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1238
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_rewrite</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Provides the functionality of <systemitem>mod_alias</systemitem> , but offers more features and flexibility. With <systemitem>mod_rewrite</systemitem> , you can redirect URLs based on multiple rules, request headers, and more."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1249
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_setenvif</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1251
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sets environment variables based on details of the client's request, such as the browser string the client sends, or the client's IP address. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1259
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_spelling</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1261
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_spelling</systemitem> attempts to automatically correct typographical errors in URLs, such as capitalization errors."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1268
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_ssl</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1270
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enables encrypted connections between Web server and clients. See <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-ssl\"/> for details. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1278
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_status</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1280
#, no-c-format
msgid "Provides information on server activity and performance under http://localhost/server-status/. For security reasons, you should always limit access to this URL. By default, only <systemitem class=\"domainname\">localhost</systemitem> is allowed to access this URL. <systemitem>mod_status</systemitem> is configured at <filename>/etc/apache2/mod_status.conf</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1291
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_suexec</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1293
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_suexec</systemitem> lets you run CGI scripts under a different user and group. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:1300
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_userdir</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1302
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enables user-specific directories available under <filename>~<replaceable>USER</replaceable>/</filename> . The <systemitem>UserDir</systemitem> directive must be specified in the configuration. This module is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1314
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multiprocessing modules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1315
#, no-c-format
msgid "&productname; provides two different multiprocessing modules (MPMs) for use with Apache:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1321
#, no-c-format
msgid "<xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-modules-mpm-prefork\" xrefstyle=\"select:title\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1326
#, no-c-format
msgid "<xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-modules-mpm-worker\" xrefstyle=\"select:title\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1332
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prefork MPM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1333
#, no-c-format
msgid "The prefork MPM implements a non-threaded, preforking Web server. It makes the Web server behave similarly to Apache version 1.x. In this version it isolates each request and handles it by forking a separate child process. Thus problematic requests cannot affect others, avoiding a lockup of the Web server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1340
#, no-c-format
msgid "While providing stability with this process-based approach, the prefork MPM consumes more system resources than its counterpart, the worker MPM. The prefork MPM is considered the default MPM for Unix-based operating systems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1347
#, no-c-format
msgid "MPMs in this document"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1348
#, no-c-format
msgid "This document assumes Apache is used with the prefork MPM."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1354
#, no-c-format
msgid "Worker MPM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1355
#, no-c-format
msgid "The worker MPM provides a multi-threaded Web server. A thread is a <quote>lighter</quote> form of a process. The advantage of a thread over a process is its lower resource consumption. Instead of only forking child processes, the worker MPM serves requests by using threads with server processes. The preforked child processes are multi-threaded. This approach makes Apache perform better by consuming fewer system resources than the prefork MPM."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1364
#, no-c-format
msgid "One major disadvantage is the stability of the worker MPM: if a thread becomes corrupt, all threads of a process can be affected. In the worst case, this may result in a server crash. Especially when using the Common Gateway Interface (CGI) with Apache under heavy load, internal server errors might occur because of threads being unable to communicate with system resources. Another argument against using the worker MPM with Apache is that not all available Apache modules are thread-safe and thus cannot be used with the worker MPM."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1375
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using PHP modules with MPMs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1376
#, no-c-format
msgid "Not all available PHP modules are thread-safe. Using the worker MPM with <systemitem>mod_php</systemitem> is strongly discouraged."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1385
#, no-c-format
msgid "External modules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1386
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find a list of all external modules shipped with &productname; here. Find the module's documentation in the listed directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1394
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adds support to Apache to provide &aa; confinement to individual CGI scripts handled by modules like <systemitem>mod_php&php-version;</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: member
#: apache2.xml:1399
#, no-c-format
msgid "Package Name: <systemitem>apache2-mod_apparmor</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: member
#: apache2.xml:1400
#, no-c-format
msgid "More Information: <xref linkend=\"part-apparmor\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1408
#, no-c-format
msgid "PHP is a server-side, cross-platform HTML embedded scripting language."
msgstr ""

