#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1533
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apache configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1534
#, no-c-format
msgid "In &productname;, the execution of CGI scripts is only allowed in the directory <filename>/srv/www/cgi-bin/</filename> . This location is already configured to execute CGI scripts. If you have created a virtual host configuration (see <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-configuration-manually-vhost\"/> ) and want to place your scripts in a host-specific directory, you must unlock and configure this directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1544
#, no-c-format
msgid "VirtualHost CGI configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1545
#, no-c-format
msgid "ScriptAlias /cgi-bin/ \"/srv/www/&wwwname;/cgi-bin/\"<co xml:id=\"co-apache2-cgi-script-alias\"/>\n"
      "\n"
      "&lt;Directory \"/srv/www/&wwwname;/cgi-bin/\"&gt;\n"
      " Options +ExecCGI<co xml:id=\"co-apache2-cgi-options\"/>\n"
      " AddHandler cgi-script .cgi .pl<co xml:id=\"co-apache2-cgi-handler\"/>\n"
      " Require all granted<co xml:id=\"co-apache2-cgi-order\"/>\n"
      "&lt;/Directory&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1554
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tells Apache to handle all files within this directory as CGI scripts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1559
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enables CGI script execution"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1564
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tells the server to treat files with the extensions .pl and .cgi as CGI scripts. Adjust according to your needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1570
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <systemitem>Require</systemitem> directive controls the default access state. In this case, access is granted to the specified directory without limitation. For more information on authentication and authorization, see <link xlink:href=\"https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/howto/auth.html\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1583
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running an example script"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1584
#, no-c-format
msgid "CGI programming differs from <quote>regular</quote> programming in that the CGI programs and scripts must be preceded by a MIME-Type header such as <literal>Content-type: text/html</literal> . This header is sent to the client, so it understands what kind of content it receives. Secondly, the script's output must be something the client, usually a Web browser, understands&mdash;HTML or plain text or images, for example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1592
#, no-c-format
msgid "A simple test script available under <filename>/usr/share/doc/packages/apache2/test-cgi</filename> is part of the Apache package. It outputs the content of certain environment variables as plain text. Copy this script to either <filename>/srv/www/cgi-bin/</filename> or the script directory of your virtual host ( <filename>/srv/www/&wwwname;/cgi-bin/</filename> ) and name it <filename>test.cgi</filename> . Edit the file to have <literal>#!/bin/sh</literal> as the first line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1602
#, no-c-format
msgid "Files accessible by the Web server should be owned by the user <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> . For additional information see <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-security\"/> . Because the Web server runs with a different user, the CGI scripts must be world-executable and world-readable. Change into the CGI directory and use the command <command>chmod 755 test.cgi</command> to apply the proper permissions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1610
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now call <literal>http://localhost/cgi-bin/test.cgi</literal> or <literal>http://&wwwname;/cgi-bin/test.cgi</literal> . You should see the <quote>CGI/1.0 test script report</quote> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1619
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you do not see the output of the test program but an error message instead, check the following:"
