msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1649
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make sure that the script does not contain programming errors. If you have not changed <filename>test.cgi</filename> , this should not be the case, but if you are using your own programs, always make sure that they do not contain programming errors."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1660
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting up a secure Web server with SSL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1662
#, no-c-format
msgid "Whenever sensitive data, such as credit card information, is transferred between Web server and client, it is desirable to have a secure, encrypted connection with authentication. <systemitem>mod_ssl</systemitem> provides strong encryption using the secure sockets layer (SSL) and transport layer security (TLS) protocols for HTTP communication between a client and the Web server. Using TLS/SSL, a private connection between Web server and client is established. Data integrity is ensured and client and server can authenticate each other."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1673
#, no-c-format
msgid "For this purpose, the server sends an SSL certificate that holds information proving the server's valid identity before any request to a URL is answered. In turn, this guarantees that the server is the uniquely correct end point for the communication. Additionally, the certificate generates an encrypted connection between client and server that can transport information without the risk of exposing sensitive, plain-text content."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1682
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>mod_ssl</systemitem> does not implement the TLS/SSL protocols itself, but acts as an interface between Apache and an SSL library. In &productname;, the OpenSSL library is used. OpenSSL is automatically installed with Apache."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1689
#, no-c-format
msgid "The most visible effect of using <systemitem>mod_ssl</systemitem> with Apache is that URLs are prefixed with <literal>https://</literal> instead of <literal>http://</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1696
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating an SSL certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1697
#, no-c-format
msgid "To use TLS/SSL with the Web server, you need to create an SSL certificate. This certificate is needed for the authorization between Web server and client, so that each party can identify the other party. To ensure the integrity of the certificate, it must be signed by a party every user trusts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1704
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are three types of certificates you can create: a <quote>test</quote> certificate for testing purposes only, a self-signed certificate for a defined circle of users that trust you, and a certificate signed by an independent, publicly known certificate authority (CA)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1710
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a certificate is a two step process. First, a private key for the certificate authority is generated then the server certificate is signed with this key."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1717
#, no-c-format
msgid "To learn more about concepts and definitions of TLS/SSL, refer to <link xlink:href=\"https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/ssl/ssl_intro.html\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1723
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a <quote>test</quote> certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1724
#, no-c-format
msgid "To generate a test certificate, call the script <command>/usr/bin/gensslcert</command> . It creates or overwrites the files listed below. Use <command>gensslcert</command> 's optional switches to fine-tune the certificate. Call <command>/usr/bin/gensslcert </command> <option>-h</option> for more information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1733
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/etc/apache2/ssl.crt/ca.crt</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1738
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/etc/apache2/ssl.crt/server.crt</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1743
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/etc/apache2/ssl.key/server.key</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1748
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/etc/apache2/ssl.csr/server.csr</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1753
#, no-c-format
msgid "A copy of <filename>ca.crt</filename> is also placed at <filename>/srv/www/htdocs/CA.crt</filename> for download."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1758
#, no-c-format
msgid "For testing purposes only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1759
#, no-c-format
msgid "A test certificate should never be used on a production system. Only use it for testing purposes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1766
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a self-signed certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1767
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you are setting up a secure Web server for an intranet or for a defined circle of users, it is sufficient to sign a certificate with your own certificate authority (CA). Visitors to such a site will see a warning like <quote>this is an untrusted site</quote> , as Web browsers do not recognize self-signed certificates."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1775
#, no-c-format
msgid "Self-signed certificates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1776
#, no-c-format
msgid "Only use a self-signed certificate on a Web server that is accessed by people who know and trust you as a certificate authority. It is not recommended to use such a certificate for a public shop, for example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1782
#, no-c-format
msgid "First you need to generate a certificate signing request (CSR). You are going to use <command>openssl</command> , with <literal>PEM</literal> as the certificate format. During this step, you will be asked for a passphrase, and to answer several questions. Remember the passphrase you enter as you will need it in the future."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1789
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;openssl req -new &gt; new.cert.csr\n"
      "Generating a 1024 bit RSA private key\n"
      "..++++++\n"
      ".........++++++\n"
      "writing new private key to 'privkey.pem'\n"
      "Enter PEM pass phrase:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-pass1\"/>\n"
      "Verifying - Enter PEM pass phrase:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-pass2\"/>\n"
      "-----\n"
      "You are about to be asked to enter information that will be incorporated\n"
      "into your certificate request.\n"
      "What you are about to enter is what is called a Distinguished Name or a DN.\n"
      "There are quite a few fields but you can leave some blank\n"
      "For some fields there will be a default value,\n"
      "If you enter '.', the field will be left blank.\n"
      "-----\n"
      "Country Name (2 letter code) [AU]:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-country\"/>\n"
      "State or Province Name (full name) [Some-State]:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-state\"/>\n"
      "Locality Name (eg, city) []:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-city\"/>\n"
      "Organization Name (eg, company) [Internet Widgits Pty Ltd]:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-org\"/>\n"
      "Organizational Unit Name (eg, section) []:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-uname\"/>\n"
      "Common Name (for example server FQDN, or YOUR name) []:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-cname\"/>\n"
      "Email Address []:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-email\"/>\n"
      "\n"
      "Please enter the following 'extra' attributes\n"
      "to be sent with your certificate request\n"
      "A challenge password []:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-challenge\"/>\n"
      "An optional company name []:<co xml:id=\"co-ssl-self-optional\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1818
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in your passphrase."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1823
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill it in once more (and remember it)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1828
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in your 2 letter country code, such as <literal>GB</literal> or <literal>CZ</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1834
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in the name of the state where you live."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1839
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in the city name, such as <literal>Prague</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1844
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in the name of the organization you work for."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1849
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in your organization unit, or leave blank if you have none."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1854
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in either the domain name of the server, or your first and last name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1860
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in your work e-mail address."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1865
#, no-c-format
msgid "Leave the challenge password empty, otherwise you need to enter it every time you restart the Apache Web server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1871
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in the optional company name, or leave blank."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1876
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now you can generate the certificate. You are going to use <command>openssl</command> again, and the format of the certificate is the default <literal>PEM</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1882
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generating the certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1884
#, no-c-format
msgid "Export the private part of the key to <filename>new.cert.key</filename> . You will be prompted for the passphrase you entered when creating the certificate signing request (CSR)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1889
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;openssl rsa -in privkey.pem -out new.cert.key"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1892
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generate the public part of the certificate according to the information you filled out in the signing request. The <option>-days</option> option specifies the length of time before the certificate expires. You can revoke a certificate, or replace one before it expires."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1898
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;openssl x509 -in new.cert.csr -out new.cert.cert -req \\\n"
      "-signkey new.cert.key -days 365"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1902
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy the certificate files to the relevant directories, so that the Apache server can read them. Make sure that the private key <filename>/etc/apache2/ssl.key/server.key</filename> is not world-readable, while the public PEM certificate <filename>/etc/apache2/ssl.crt/server.crt</filename> is."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1909
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;cp new.cert.cert /etc/apache2/ssl.crt/server.crt\n"
      "&prompt.sudo;cp new.cert.key /etc/apache2/ssl.key/server.key"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1914
#, no-c-format
msgid "Public certificate location"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1915
#, no-c-format
msgid "The last step is to copy the public certificate file from <filename>/etc/apache2/ssl.crt/server.crt</filename> to a location where your users can access it to incorporate it into the list of known and trusted CAs in their Web browsers. Otherwise a browser complains that the certificate was issued by an unknown authority."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1925
#, no-c-format
msgid "Getting an officially signed certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1926
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are several official certificate authorities that sign your certificates. The certificate is signed by a trustworthy third party, so can be fully trusted. Publicly operating secure Web servers usually have an officially signed certificate. A list of the most used Certificate Authorities (CAs) is available at <link xlink:href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Certificate_authority#Providers\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1935
#, no-c-format
msgid "When requesting an officially signed certificate, you do not send a certificate to the CA. Instead, issue a Certificate Signing Request <!-- 2015-08-24, tbazant: replacing CA.sh with openssl (http://doccomments.provo.novell.com/comments/28367) (CSR). To create a CSR, call the script <command>/usr/share/ssl/misc/CA.sh -newreq</command>. --> (CSR). To create a CSR, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1947
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;openssl req -new -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes -keyout newkey.pem -out newreq.pem"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1948
#, no-c-format
msgid "<!-- First the script asks for a password with which the CSR should be encrypted. --> You are asked to enter a distinguished name. This requires you to answer a few questions, such as country name or organization name. Enter valid data&mdash;everything you enter here later shows up in the certificate and is checked. You do not need to answer every question. If one does not apply to you or you want to leave it blank, use <quote>.</quote> . Common name is the name of the CA itself&mdash;choose a significant name, such as <replaceable>My company</replaceable> CA. Last, a challenge password and an alternative company name must be entered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1960
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find the CSR in the directory from which you called the script. The file is named <filename>newreq.pem</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1968
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Apache with SSL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1969
#, no-c-format
msgid "The default port for TLS/SSL requests on the Web server side is 443. There is no conflict between a <quote>regular</quote> Apache listening on port 80 and an TLS/SSL-enabled Apache listening on port 443. In fact, HTTP and HTTPS can be run with the same Apache instance. Usually separate virtual hosts are used to dispatch requests to port 80 and port 443 to separate virtual servers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1978
#, no-c-format
msgid "Firewall configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1979
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not forget to open the firewall for SSL-enabled Apache on port 443. This can be done with &firewalld; as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-security-firewall-firewalld-cmd\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1985
#, no-c-format
msgid "The SSL module is enabled by default in the global server configuration. In case it has been disabled on your host, activate it with the following command: <command>a2enmod ssl</command> . To finally enable SSL, the server needs to be started with the flag <quote>SSL</quote> . To do so, call <command>a2enflag SSL</command> (case-sensitive!). If you have chosen to encrypt your server certificate with a password, you should also increase the value for <systemitem>APACHE_TIMEOUT</systemitem> in <filename>/etc/sysconfig/apache2</filename> , so you have enough time to enter the passphrase when Apache starts. Restart the server to make these changes active. A reload is not sufficient."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1997
#, no-c-format
msgid "The virtual host configuration directory contains a template <filename>/etc/apache2/vhosts.d/vhost-ssl.template</filename> with SSL-specific directives that are extensively documented. Refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-configuration-manually-vhost\"/> for the general virtual host configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2004
#, no-c-format
msgid "To get started, copy the template to <filename>/etc/apache2/vhosts.d/<replaceable>MYSSL-HOST</replaceable>.conf</filename> and edit it. Adjusting the values for the following directives should be sufficient:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2012
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>DocumentRoot</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2017
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>ServerName</systemitem>"
msgstr ""

