#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:2038
#, no-c-format
msgid "Name-based virtual hosts and SSL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2039
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default it is not possible to run multiple SSL-enabled virtual hosts on a server with only one IP address. Name-based virtual hosting requires that Apache knows which server name has been requested. The problem with SSL connections is, that such a request can only be read after the SSL connection has already been established (by using the default virtual host). As a result, users will receive a warning message stating that the certificate does not match the server name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2048
#, no-c-format
msgid "&productname; comes with an extension to the SSL protocol called Server Name Indication (SNI) addresses this issue by sending the name of the virtual domain as part of the SSL negotiation. This enables the server to <quote>switch</quote> to the correct virtual domain early and present the browser the correct certificate."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2055
#, no-c-format
msgid "SNI is enabled by default on &productname;. To enable Name-Based Virtual Hosts for SSL, configure the server as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-apache2-configuration-manually-vhost-named-vhosts\"/> (you need to use port <literal>443</literal> rather than port <literal>80</literal> with SSL)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:2063
#, no-c-format
msgid "SNI browser support"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2064
#, no-c-format
msgid "SNI must also be supported on the client side. However, SNI is supported by most browsers, except for certain older browsers. For more information, see <link xlink:href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Server_Name_Indication#Support\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2070
#, no-c-format
msgid "To configure handling of non-SNI capable browsers, use the directive <systemitem>SSLStrictSNIVHostCheck</systemitem> . When set to <literal>on</literal> in the server configuration, non-SNI capable browser will be rejected for all virtual hosts. When set to <literal>on</literal> within a <systemitem>VirtualHost</systemitem> directive, access to this particular host will be rejected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2078
#, no-c-format
msgid "When set to <literal>off</literal> in the server configuration, the server will behave as if not having SNI support. SSL requests will be handled by the <emphasis>first</emphasis> virtual host defined (for port 443)."
msgstr ""

